paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses the relationship between retinol levels and skin cancer risk, mentioning a variant in the TTR gene associated with retinol transport.

functional_data.summary: The variant rs1667226 in the TTR gene is mentioned as being associated with retinol transport.

variants.additional_notes: The variant is mentioned in the context of its role in retinol transport, not in disease association.
key_quotes: The second strongest SNP rs1667226 is in an intron of the transthyretin (TTR) gene which encodes a carrier protein that binds to a range of transport proteins including RBP4.

challenges: The paper primarily focuses on retinol and skin cancer, with limited information on TTR variants.
extraction_metadata.notes: The paper does not provide detailed penetrance or clinical data for the TTR variant.
